subSubSection.paragraph:
Coloration.
Body brown with yellowish spots (
Fig. 3A–B
). Face yellowish brown with black spots (
Figs. 3C
, 
4C–D
). Ocelli yellow. Dorsal surface of fastigium verticis, internal margins of antennal scoket, scape, pedicelli and dorsum of head black, flagellar segments with brownish rings (
Figs. 3C
, 
4C–D
). Tegmina black brown with apieces pale (
Figs. 1H–I
, 
2G–H
). Disc of pronotum with irregularly yellowish brown spots; mesonotum, metanotum and dorsal surface with short, yellowish brown stripes (
Fig. 4B, F
). Abdominal sternites, basal half of femora, apical half of tibiae and tarsi yellowish brown (
Fig. 4A–E
).
